To upload your built app APKs as a new release on GitHub, follow these steps:

### 1. Wait for the build to finish
Wait for your active terminal command `flutter build apk --release --split-per-abi` to complete.

### 2. Locate the generated APK files
Once the build is complete, you can find the generated APK files in this directory:
`build\app\outputs\flutter-apk\`

You will see files named similarly to:
* `app-armeabi-v7a-release.apk`
* `app-arm64-v8a-release.apk`
* `app-x86_64-release.apk`

### 3. Create the Release on GitHub
1. Open the link in your browser: [GitHub New Release](https://github.com/vincentagbuya03/agridirect/releases/new)
2. Click **Choose a tag**, type a version number (e.g., `v1.0.0`), and click **Create new tag**.
3. Set a **Release title** (e.g., `Release v1.0.0`) and optionally add a description of the changes.
4. Scroll down to the box labeled **"Attach binaries by dropping them here or selecting them"**.
5. Drag and drop the APK files from your `build\app\outputs\flutter-apk\` folder into that box.
6. Once the upload completes, click **Publish release**.